1.title: See Dad Nail Valentine's Day
1.plot: Joe fears the Hobbs men suffer from a curse when he prepares for a date with Amnada. David hides a necklace for Marcus but, Amy mistakenly thinks it for her.

2.title: See Dad Downsize
2.plot: David thinks that the house is cluttered and asks everyone to make some sacrifices; Kevin tracks down another "See Dad Run" fan.

3.title: See Dad Run Joe Into Detention
3.plot: David lets Joe play hooky; feeling guilty, Joe reveals the truth; Amy and Emily want to learn which neighbor is not cleaning up after their dog.

4.title: See Dad Teach Emily to Drive
4.plot: David thinks Emily is not ready to drive when his coaching makes her nervous; Janie discovers that Dr. Monkey Chunks was run over in the driveway.

5.title: See Dad Run Into Marcus' Nephew
5.plot: After being forbidden to drive at night, Emily takes Amy's car and goes to a party; Joe wants more responsibility.

6.title: See Dad Rough It
6.plot: David takes Joe's scout troop on a camping trip with help from his old crew.

7.title: See Dad Ruin Joe's Teacher
7.plot: After Joe's favorite teacher quits to follow his dream, David tries to get the teacher back.

8.title: See Dad Lose the Forest for the Treehouse
8.plot: David decides to help Joe build a tree house; Emily gets her first job on Amy's set.

9.title: See Dad Become Room Mom
9.plot: David has a hard time leaving Janie at school and becomes room mom. When he realizes how much work it is, he causes mayhem to get out of it. Meanwhile, Joe runs away from a scary older student on his first day of 7th grade.

10.title: See Dad Live at Five
10.plot: David gets Emily an internship at a news show, and she loves it so much she considers dropping out of school. Meanwhile, Joe and his friends prepare for their talent show performance. Guest Star: Nicole Sullivan

11.title: See Dad Watch Janie Run Away
11.plot: When Janie refuses to follow David's rules, she runs away to Marcus' house and David tries everything to get her to come back home. Meanwhile, Emily tries to take advantage of Joe to get close to his new older friend.

12.title: See Dad Fire Original Katie... Again
12.plot: David's former co-star who he fired from the show becomes Joe's slightly unhinged Spanish tutor. When Joe's grades suffer, David gets her a job on Amy's soap opera, where things go from bad to worse. Guest Star: Daniella Monet

13.title: See Dad Get in the Ring
13.plot: David challenges a wrestler to a televised event in order to impress Joe and his friends.

14.title: See Dad Rest His Case
14.plot: David finally impresses his father-in-law by serving on jury duty; the children must go through the Major's boot camp.

15.title: See Dad Runner Up
15.plot: Still trying to avoid her boss, Amy is forced to deal with him directly when Emily competes in a beauty pageant against his daughter. Joe is forced to enlist Kevin and Marcus as video game teammates leading to some interesting gardening.

16.title: See Dad Jump
16.plot: David tries to make Joe realize he needs to complete things and agrees to jump out of a plane if Joe complete a project.

17.title: See Dad's Mom with Mom's Dad
17.plot: Janie invites David's mother and Amy's father to attend grandparents' day at her school; David demands that his mother and Amy's father stop fighting and try to get along.

18.title: See Dad Overreact
18.plot: When David begins acting differently around Janie, she becomes worried that she is going to be given away; Joe and Amy are trapped in an elevator with Joe's hero.

1.title: See Dad Run Home
1.plot: David Hobbs has spent the last decade playing a beloved father on one of TV's biggest sitcoms. When his series ends, he transitions into a stay-at-home dad watching over his children, Emily, Janie, and Joe. Meanwhile, his wife, Amy, returns to her television career. Now, David must accustom to tending to his kids' every need. His children worry since he is never around, and barely knows anything about being a parent. David soon realizes how challenging it is to be an actual father.

2.title: See Dad Lose Janie
2.plot: David has to take Emily and Joe to school and take Janie to Mommy and Me class and get everybody home in time for a much-anticipated piano lesson. Meanwhile, Emily has ruined Amy's favorite sweater and asks David to pay for it in exchange for finding Janie.

3.title: See Dad Play Coach
3.plot: David tries his best to suppress his competitive nature when he takes over as head coach of Joe's rag-tag baseball team. Emily conducts an experiment on her parents for a school paper.

4.title: See Dad Rise from the Dead
4.plot: After Joe bails out of yet another sleepover, David goes to great lengths to help him conquer his fear of all things scary in order to keep him out of David and Amy's bed at night.

5.title: See Dad Get Wah-Wah'd
5.plot: David and Marcus are producing a new TV show and try to get Ricky Adams (James Maslow), an actor who played David's son on his old TV show to star in it. However, Ricky's self-centered attitude annoys David. Amy is reluctant to get reading glasses.

6.title: See Dad Meet Matthew Pearson
6.plot: Emily's latest crush, Matthew Pearson, is more interested in spending time with David than her.

7.title: See Dad One Night Only
7.plot: David and Amy learn that Emily will be an extra in the school play. But after the director learns that Emily is David's daughter, she is then given the lead role, despite the fact that she is a terrible actress. Joe and Janie try to make a viral video.

8.title: See Dad Catch a Rat
8.plot: David tries to catch a rat loose in the house without the help of an exterminator. He also lies to Emily saying that he will catch it humanely since she is now a member of an animal rights group. Amy is not pleased with David having his reclining chair from his old TV show in the house so she tries to get rid of it.

9.title: See Dad Run Christmas Into the Ground
9.plot: When Amy has to work on Christmas Eve, David promises to take care of everything but the stress of making the holiday perfect for the kids gets to him and he temporarily loses track of what Christmas is really about.

10.title: See Dad Campaign
10.plot: When David discovers that Emily is running for class president against the son of his rival, he embeds himself in her campaign but Amy and Emily surprise him by leaning on superstar Ricky Adams to help her win.

11.title: See Dad Get Schooled
11.plot: When Joe wants to participate in his school's father/son history bowl competition, David realizes he doesn't know anything on the subject and learns he never actually passed history in school. The family sets out to teach David the facts.

12.title: See Dad Assist Kevin
12.plot: The Hobbs family must take care of Kevin when he injures himself, but Kevin feels like a burden to them and takes off. They eventually find him, learning much more about Kevin in the process and are inspired to help him.

13.title: See Dad Run, But He Can't Hide
13.plot: A stalking paparazzi captures a few innocent photos of David but manipulates them to make him look like a horrible Dad. Meanwhile, Amy feigns indifference when the paparazzi don't recognize her.

14.title: See Dad Get Married and Married
14.plot: When Amy learns about David's first wedding, she's jealous of the exotic affair compared to their quickie-ceremony so David and the kids set out to give her the wedding she deserves.

15.title: See Dad as the Great and Powerful Hobbs
15.plot: When David and Amy learn their security system has a surveillance feature, and they allow Emily to have a party, they must decide how much supervision they want to have over their daughter.

16.title: See Dad Play Hard to Get
16.plot: When David decides to play hard to get while renegotiating a spokesman contract - and gives the same advice to Emily - his strategy doesn't work out as he planned in either case and he must fix the mess he's made for his daughter.

17.title: See Dad Get Janie Into Kindergarten
17.plot: Janie wants to join her friend Charlotte in Kindergarten next year, so the family begins the application process, including a surprise home-visit from the principal at the worst possible time.

18.title: See Dad Host a Play Group
18.plot: While observing the many different parenting styles of the moms at a playgroup for Janie, David realizes he needs to find a technique of his own. He tries out different styles on the kids until they finally stage an intervention

19.title: See Dad Get Attacked by Promzilla
19.plot: When Amy has to work the weekend Emily and Mary are getting ready for Prom, dress shopping duties fall on David and Marcus, who let things spiral out of control. Now the guys must find a way to give the girls a Prom to remember.

20.title: See Dad See Through Grandma
20.plot: David prepares a special Mother's Day for Amy, but his plans are hampered when his narcissistic mother arrives and steals the spotlight.

1.title: See Dad Swoon
1.plot: When Joe gets invited out by his lab partner Amanda, he turns to David for advice on how to say no. But when David learns her dad is his golf hero, his own man-crush takes over and he forgets about helping Joe with his.

2.title: See Dad Get the Family to the Airport
2.plot: David decides to take the family on an impromptu trip, but with Amy meeting them at the airport, he's got six hours to pack the bags and get the kids there without incident. What could possibly go wrong?

3.title: See Dad Be Normal.Ish
3.plot: Joe's in the spotlight after a heroic action, but finds it hard to go back to being regular Joe when his 15 minutes of fame end so David tries to show him being "normal" can be fun. Janie discovers what Emily's been hiding.

4.title: See Dad Throw a Birthday Party
4.plot: Janie's birthday venue cancels last minute and David becomes party planner. To top Janie's friend Charlotte's amazing party, David plans a birthday bash complete with a famous monkey, Guest Star

5.title: See Dad McLivin' with the McGinleys
5.plot: David's nemesis, Ted McGinley, has a new reality show and challenges the Hobbs to let him and his family live with them for three days. Meanwhile, Marcus and Kevin get locked in the soundproof basement.

6.title: See Dad Have Chemistry
6.plot: David and Janie audition for a commercial, and Janie wins the role, but David lacks "dad chemistry." Now he must prove he's the best dad for Janie offscreen and on. Meanwhile, Emily tries spontaneity to win over a new friend.

7.title: See Dad Run a Fever
7.plot: David's booked to guest on a popular talk show, but when a virus sweeps the family, he has to fight to stay healthy. During the show, the host falls ill with the same bug, and David finds himself painfully hosting alone.

8.title: See Dad Send Emily Flowers
8.plot: When a girl gives Emily a hard time about not having a date to the school dance, David sends her flowers but the note gets lost and she thinks she has a secret admirer forcing David to come up with a plan.

9.title: See Dad Run Halloween
9.plot: David hopes to get the kids in the Halloween spirit, so he takes them with him to "exorcise" the Ghost of Stage 19. The kids aren't impressed until crazy things start happening at home, and the whole family is freaked out.

10.title: See Dad Dance Around the Truth
10.plot: David picks Janie up from dance and sees that she's awful but enthusiastic! So he does what any dad would: tells her how to make it to the top - nearly causing a classmate injury. Amy's job is a bad influence on Emily's friends.

11.title: See Dad See Dad Run
11.plot: David's TV dad Bernie visits, but the reunion sours when he runs off and leaves his new baby. David must convince Bernie that being a real dad will be his best role. Parenting a fake baby for class is more than Emily can handle.

12.title: See Dad Have a Career
12.plot: For his school career day video, Joe features David in his new habitat as stay-at-home dad, but the montage makes David believe life is dull since quitting TV, so the family must rally to show him how much his new job matters.

13.title: See Dad See Joe Sleepwalk
13.plot: Joe is sleepwalking due to first kiss with Amanda nerves, but David thinks he's nervous about a fight at school and gives him terrible first kiss advice. Meanwhile, a lonely Marcus is living with the Hobbs with his wife away.

14.title: See Dad Run Until He Drops
14.plot: Marcus' wife, Alicia, arrives home from Europe surprising everyone with her new look but the Hobbs can't keep up with their old friend's new lifestyle! Joe abandons his old friends in search of a dance trophy at school.

15.title: See Dad Roast the Toast
15.plot: The Hobbs reluctantly attend an anniversary weekend party for his cousin, Fred, only to discover that once again Fred has taken advantage of David's star power to enjoy all of the "perks," leaving David to plan his revenge.

locations: Paramount Studios - 5555 Melrose Avenue, Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA
imdb.plot outline: After a decade on television, actor David Hobbs becomes a stay-at-home dad so his soap-opera star wife can get back in the spotlight, but he quickly realizes that playing a dad on television is much different from the real thing. He has to take care of his three kids, Emily, Joe and Janie with the help of his best friends, Marcus and Kevin.

synopsis: David Hobbs has been America's favorite Dad for the past 10 years, but that is all coming to an end. As David says goodbye to his life of sitcom T.V., reality awaits him at home with his wife and three kids. When the stay-at-home parent roles switch, David must learn the ins and outs of being a house-dad, while his wife Amy returns to the big screen. Suddenly, looking after three quirky kids and keeping their home in check becomes his newest starring role!More about the characters:David HobbsDavid has spent the last 10 years playing the perfect dad on T.V. and seems to have forgotten how to master his real-life role of "world's best dad". Now that his wife has gone back to work, it's David's turn to takeover at home and life with his three kids proves to be one crazy adventure! He has a lot to learn, but his love for his family, quick thinking, and good sense of humor becomes the perfect recipe for this new journey.Amy HobbsThis is one super-mom you don't want to mess with! Amy will do anything for her children, but her decision to return back to the big screen means a little less time at home. While the idea of leaving her babies to the care of David puts her stomach in jitters, her support and love for him conquers all. Between picking up her old career and maintaining a full house, its easy to say her life certainly isn't is dull.Emily HobbsEmily Hobbs is sister to Joe and Janie, and the eldest of the three Hobbs kids. While she deals with the everyday drama that comes with being a teenager, her biggest dilemma revolves around a patchy relationship with her dear ol' dad, David.Joe HobbsJoe is the middle child of the Hobbs clan, which might explain some of his wacky actions. Though he can take himself a little too seriously at times (he hates being late!), it doesn't stop him from all the fun that comes with being a kid.Janie HobbsJanie is sweet as pie and a real crowd pleaser. Small as she is, her age never gets in the way of her having her own voice... even if it means getting wrapped into some sticky situations from time to time!
